    "type": "consumable",
    "data": {
        "description": {
            "value": "<p><span>You set a cunning wire to trip a creature. A Medium or smaller creature that enters this snare&rsquo;s square must attempt a DC 20 Reflex save.&nbsp;<br /></span></p>\n<p><span>If you want to create a trip snare to trip a larger creature, you must create a group of contiguous snares of a length equal to the edge of that larger creature&rsquo;s space, and the creature must be moving such that it moves into the full set of snares. For example, three trip snares in a 15-foot-line can trip a Huge creature coming down a corridor into the line of snares.&nbsp;<br /></span></p>\n<p><span><strong>Critical Success</strong>&nbsp;The creature is unaffected.<br /><strong>Success</strong>&nbsp;The creature is flat-footed until the start of its next turn.<br /><strong>Failure</strong>&nbsp;The creature falls prone.<br /><strong>Critical Failure</strong>&nbsp;The creature falls prone and takes 1d6 bludgeoning damage.</span></p>",
